 Mapule Phia Rasemane (38) and her baby son Kamogelo were underway from Gauteng to Mpumalanga when she lost control of her Volkswagen Polo just after the Arnot off-ramp last week Wednesday. The car crashed through a water channel and rolled. Young Kamogalo was declared dead on the scene whilst his mother had to be cut out of the wreck and was rushed to hospital. She regained consciousness shortly after being freed from the wreckage by emergency workers. Also read: Accident claims the life of an infant According to information, Ms Rasemane was transferred from the Middelburg Hospital to the Witbank Hospital, where she was to undergo an operation. On Friday the family was informed, however, that she too had passed away. Both mother and child will be laid to rest this weekend in Tzaneen. • Another woman lost her life on the N4 on Monday morning. It is suspected that she lost control of her Toyota Etios, crashed through a barrier and went over a bridge between the Samora Machel and Hendrina off-ramps on the N4. Her vehicle crashed against a wall on the opposite side of the bridge before landing on its roof. Also read: One dead in early morning crash She was killed on impact. •Read full article in this week’s Middelburg Observer.   One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za